history.content:
If SWAP was set up with 16B and you received an error message:

Please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu including the following information: 

  • Subject: EECS 16B Swap Message
  • Please let me know if you received a message that you were not enrolled due to the swap set
  • Your SID
  • The class you set the swap with (MUST INCLUDE: Course & Course # and the Class CNN)

If you received a time conflict message please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu to inform me.

Subject line: 16B Time Conflict

If SWAP was set up with 16B and you received an error message:

Please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu including the following information: 

  • Subject: EECS 16B Swap Message
  • Please let me know if you received a message that you were not enrolled due to the swap set
  • Your SID
  • The class you set the swap with (MUST INCLUDE: Course & Course # and the Class CNN)

If you received a time conflict message please email ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu to inform me.

I am currently a declared LSCS senior who needs to take EECS 16B, and phase I waitlisted at position 573, with a swap set for a class I am currently enrolled in (Slavic 50). I noticed that recently, many from the waitlist were enrolled (in order of priority, with CS seniors with top priority), but I wasn't because there was a time conflict, even though the class with a time conflict was set to SWAP with 16B. Now I am at the very back of the waitlist (160) even though I should have been enrolled, and I need to take this class to graduate. What can I do now, who can I talk to to sort this out and enroll. Thank you!
history.subject: EECS 16B Can't Enroll
